Story.create(title:"It Was A Dark And Stormy Knight",every_word:true,body:"He looked like any other man sworn to defend the kingdom:  strong, determined, and a force to be reckoned with.  However, he had one minor distinguishing feature:  a tiny storm cloud hovering above his head.")
#Story2
Story.create(title:"An Inconvenient Invasion",every_word:true,body:"Fires raged and roiled over everything Emma saw.  She heard the metal frames of nearby automobiles scream in violation as the incensed inferno sadistically twisted them into shapes they were never meant to resemble.  She swung around, looking for anyone else who made it out, but the only movement was the shimmering air from the overwhelming heat.  As she stumbled towards the park across the street, away from the flames, she realized if They had decided to come a day or two later, she would have made her job interview and possibly have had health insurance before the invasion happened.  Half-deliriously she closed her eyes and chuckled to herself…and caught the curb with her foot, crumpling face-first into the cool grass.  “This”, Emma thought, “is really just not my day”.")
#Story3
Story.create(title:"Twilight - Round Two",every_word:true,body:"\"Hello,\" said a quiet, musical voice. I looked up, stunned that he was speaking to me. He was sitting as far away from me as the desk allowed, but his chair was angled toward me. His hair was dripping wet, disheveled — even so, he looked like he'd just finished shooting a commercial for hair gel. His dazzling face was friendly, open, a slight smile on his flawless lips. But his eyes were careful. \"My name is Edward Cullen,\" he continued. \"I didn't have a chance to introduce myself last week. You must be Bella Swan.\" My mind was spinning with confusion. Had I made up the whole thing? He was perfectly polite now. I had to speak; he was waiting. But I couldn't think of anything conventional to say.")
#Story4
Story.create(title:"It’s Over",every_word:true,body:"I packed my bags and left that night.  You can love a person through almost anything, but this was the final straw.  I wasn’t going to stand for it any longer.")
#Story5
Story.create(title:"The Sheriff’s Secret",every_word:true,body:"All the accolades at the saloon, the gentlemen tipping their hats in the street while ladies blushed and curtsied; all the respect he garnered around town was all based on a lie.  Yes, Sheriff Ambrose had collared twenty three of the most wanted bandits since he started at his post here, but while he had brought every one of the captured criminals into the station, no one could imagine the truth:  the Sheriff’s horse had done all the work.")
