Story.create(title:"Not Quite Another Day At School",every_word:true,body:"Brian jolted awake.  \"Mr. Cambell!\"  Brian opened his eyes to see a blurry figure that looked vaguely like his 2nd period English teacher looking directly at him.  \"Mr. Cambell!  I trust William Shakespeare, one of the greatest playwrights this world has ever been graced to host, is not the reason you are sleeping in my class this morning?\"  Brian thought for a second, then spoke \"Not…the only reason, Miss Peters.\"  The class tittered.  He blinked a couple more times to see his teacher’s formerly featureless face resolve into what must have been the tightest pursing of the lips he ever remembered witnessing.  And his still-sleepy grin didn’t seem to be helping.  Miss Peters finally opened her mouth, \"Detention, Brian.  Let\’s have you stay an extra hour after school to make sure you didn\’t miss any essential components of Troilus and Cressida during your nap.  Now class, let\’s ensure we don\’t have anyone else joining Brian today.\"  He sighed.  Oh well, perhaps she\’d let him get started on some homework if he apologized.  He looked out the window.  With all the snow swirling around it\’s not like staying in school a little longer was the worst thing that could happen to him.  Plus, it still looked about 20 degrees-Brian looked further left and sat up straight.  Out on south soccer field, he saw what could only be described as")
